Australian Bond Futures, N.Z. Notes Surge Following Tumble in U.S. Stocks

-- B y   C a n d i c e   Z a c h a r i a h s
-- 
2011-08-04T22:27:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/australian-bond-futures-n-z-notes-surge-following-tumble-in-u-s-stocks.html
Australian bond futures and  New
Zealand  government debt surged after a drop in U.S. stocks
yesterday spurred investor demand for the safest assets.  Australian three-year bond futures for September delivery
climbed 0.36 to 96.22, and 10-year bond contracts jumped 0.26 to
95.53 on the  Sydney Futures Exchange .  The yield on New Zealand’s two-year government note dropped
4.5 basis points to 3.23 percent, according to Bloomberg Bond
Trader data. The rate on New Zealand’s 10-year security tumbled
to 4.50 percent, the least since March 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candice Zachariahs in Sydney at 
 czachariahs2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
